{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:17:33.663359+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my investigation of the repository, here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## Runtime Profiles\n\nThe README documents **five runtime profiles**, each serving a distinct deployment/development purpose:\n\n| Profile | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| **local** | For development even when **completely offline/disconnected** from any network. |\n| **local-dev** | For connecting your local machine to the **DEV environment** remotely. |\n| **dev** | For deploying to the **Development** environment (server-side). |\n| **staging** | For deploying to the **Staging** environment. |\n| **live** | For deploying to the **Live** (production) environment. |\n\nThe `local` vs. `local-dev` split is a thoughtful distinction — `local` is fully self-contained (e.g., in-memory or embedded databases), while `local-dev` bridges your workstation to shared dev services.\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Developer Setup for Linting & Testing\n\n### Linting\n\n- **Tool:** [Spring Java Format](https://github.com/spring-io/spring-javaformat) via the `io.spring.javaformat` Gradle plugin (configured in `lint.gradle`).\n- **Lint command:** `./gradlew checkFormat`\n- **Auto-lint on every commit:** Enable the provided git pre-commit hook by running:\n  ```bash\n  git config core.hookspath .githooks\n  ```\n  The `.githooks/pre-commit` script simply runs `$GIT_DIR/gradlew checkFormat` before each commit.\n- **IDE integration:** If you use IntelliJ IDEA, the README links to the [Spring Java Format IntelliJ IDEA plugin](https://github.com/spring-io/spring-javaformat#intellij-idea) so your IDE's auto-format matches the project's lint rules.\n\n### Running Tests\n\n- **Test framework:** JUnit 5 (`junit-jupiter`) with AssertJ and Mockito.\n- **Run all CI tests:** `./gradlew test`\n- **Tag-based test suites** (defined in `build.gradle` via JUnit Platform suites):\n\n  | Task | Tag(s) | Description |\n  |---|---|---|\n  | `unitTest` | Excludes `develop`, `context`, `restdocs` | Fast, isolated, no Spring context. |\n  | `contextTest` | Includes `context` | Integration tests that boot the Spring context. |\n  | `restDocsTest` | Includes `restdocs` | Generates AsciiDoc API docs via Spring REST Docs. |\n  | `developTest` | Includes `develop` | Scratch/experimental tests excluded from CI. |\n\n- **IntelliJ IDEA tip:** Set *Build, Execution, Deployment → Build Tools → Gradle → Run tests using → **IntelliJ IDEA*** so test code runs natively in the IDE rather than through Gradle.\n\n### CI Pipeline (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`)\n\nOn pushes/PRs to `main`, CI uses **JDK 21 (Adoptium)** and runs:\n1. `./gradlew checkFormat` — lint\n2. `./gradlew test` — the default test task (which excludes `develop` and `restdocs` tags)", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 690, "prompt_tokens": 10117, "total_tokens": 10807, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 18, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9984, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0006940974, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 9.37974e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0006003}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863441-oBLo5ZwwfEkfELdOPdz0", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3bb-98bb-7ea1-9991-6f4cc1764c69-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10117, "output_tokens": 690, "total_tokens": 10807, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9984}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 18}}}}]}}}
